portfolios.definition: Sony has a large amount of web projects, that every part is carefully planned, designed and carefully developed.<new line>My work is to prepare newly requested mockups, add the functionality to the mocukps with the sample data manipulations.<new line>After testing the mockups on different devices & browsers I commit the files to both SVN and Git Repositories.<new line>If there is an inconsistency at the back-end implementation I help finding the solution to the back-end team.

Currently I work for Nexum, mostly dealing with Sony Projects at Sony office located at √úmraniye/Istanbul. In some cases I also take part on other Nexum Projects at Maslak/Istanbul when needed.<new line> I try to use the latest tools for development such as Web Storm & Sublime 3, Emmet to generate the tags of a needed module or some templating engines that takes of many html or cshtml files in a single touch which are generally based on Razor Templating Engine, Node.js and Grunt Automation scripts.

I was one of the six Front-end developers  that were dealing with the implementation issues on the web page renewal of Tuekcell, the project called SingleHub.<new line>I mostly dealed with the Js and Css issues of newly produced pages, cross-browser compatibility problems, ie memory leaks caused by the bootstrap js libraries and etc.<new line>SingleHub is a project that combines many distrubuted sites of the company together to give the customers a better user experience.

KG TEKNOLOJI is a rapidly expanding IT consulting organization to provide a wide range of information communication technology and high quality consulting services.<new line>I worked on an outsource project for Turkcell as a consultant front-end developer at KG. I mostly dealed with the issues that were assigned to me via HP-Alm client and worked with other consultants from other companies to build the web project of Turkcell.<new line>There were analysists, back-end developers (mostly JAVA), testers and business analysists.<new line>Our development enviroment was based on the eclipse ide, weblogic, and jsp based web apps. I had an experience on tiles, jstl, maven, jar packages and such Java related things on that project.

I was one of the co-founders of Inventus Bili≈üim Hizmetleri A.≈û. that intended to give life to a start-up project named adresin.com that aimed to solve many problems of the real esate related sites.<new line>I dealed with the design side mostly and after the design period with many mockup and idea changes I started the generation of html, css and js files for templating them with drupal.<new line>I had the experience of a start-up project and the hard parts of building fom scratch,  I met with the guy √ñnder √ñzkan who was our CTO and was very talented nearly at all web technologies made me have a deeper understanding of web technologies and concepts.<new line>I learned to work with scrum, sprint, product owner,daily scrum meetings and such aglie things that made our project much more sustainable.

I converted PSD design files to Html, css and javascript codes for a Facebook app that Aygaz published for mothers day.<new line>Html elements such as file inputs or text inputs were customised as seen in the design files, and the flow was leaded by Javascript, being controlled by Drupal interface at the administration panel.<new line>Users could easily create a sample facebook page which had the famous events of their childhood and print out as a pdf or such format.
